# Verification Architecture

A mailbox-based SystemVerilog verification environment is used to verify APB functionality.

```text
              +-------------+
              | Generator   |
              +------+------+
                     |
                     | mailbox
                     v
              +-------------+
              | Driver      |
              +------+------+
                     |
                     v
               APB Interface
                     |
                     v
                DUT (RTL)
                     |
                     v
              +-------------+
              | Monitor     |
              +------+------+
                     |
                     | mailbox
                     v
              +-------------+
              | Scoreboard  |
              +-------------+

                     |
                     v

              +-------------+
              | Coverage    |
              +-------------+

              +-------------+
              | Assertions  |
              +-------------+
```

---

## Verification Components

### Generator
- Creates constrained-random APB transactions
- Generates read, write, and error scenarios

### Driver
- Converts transactions into pin-level APB activity
- Drives DUT inputs through the interface

### Monitor
- Observes APB bus activity
- Captures completed transactions

### Scoreboard
- Maintains reference memory model
- Compares DUT responses against expected values

### Functional Coverage
Tracks:
- Read transactions
- Write transactions
- Address ranges
- Error responses
- Cross coverage

### Assertions (SVA)
Checks:
- PSEL asserted before PENABLE
- Stable address during ACCESS phase
- Stable write data during ACCESS phase
- Correct transaction completion behavior

